message.entry: System must be a valid model or subsystem name.
Unable to replace block with specified block ''{0}''. Specify a valid block type or mask type or ensure the library that contains ''{0}'' is loaded.
Unable to replace blocks of type ''{0}''. Specify a valid block type.

The model must be unlocked to make changes to it. To unlock the model, use the Simulink Toolstrip or enter the command: \nset_param(bdroot(System),'Lock','off'), \nwhere System is the name of the system passed to replace_block.
